    "attributes": {
        "action": "Ban schools from requiring students to take a modern foreign language GCSE",
        "additional_details": "The Government should make modern foreign languages (MFL) optional for GCSE. Students should have the freedom to focus on subjects they're passionate about, reducing stress and promoting well-being. Offering choice in language learning can lead to more motivated students and better outcomes overall. Let's empower our youth to pursue their interests and strengths.",
        "background": "Schools should not be able to force students to take modern foreign languages as a GCSE, it must be a option in all schools.",
